# alternative-splicing-nextflow — task tracking

## Status vs Eleni's pipeline (last reviewed May 2026)

Eleni's pipeline is a script-based (non-Nextflow) workflow that runs rMATS + MAJIQ
and generates downstream plots and analyses with ad-hoc R/Python scripts.

### Where we now match or exceed Eleni

| Feature                                  | Eleni | Us         |
|------------------------------------------|-------|------------|
| rMATS-turbo (5 event types)              | ✅    | ✅          |
| MAJIQ deltaPSI                           | ✅    | ✅ (V3 API) |
| IsoformSwitchAnalyzeR                    | ❌    | ✅          |
| Sashimi plots (rmats2sashimiplot)        | ✅    | ✅          |
| GO/KEGG enrichment (clusterProfiler)     | ✅    | ✅          |
| PEGASAS pathway-splicing correlation     | ✅    | ✅ (Py3 port)|
| Cross-tool overlap (UpSetR)              | ✅    | ✅          |
| PSI PCA (per-sample IncLevel matrix)     | ✅    | ✅          |
| Splice junction QC section               | ❌    | ✅          |
| Event prioritization score               | ❌    | ✅          |
| DE + AS integration (dual-hit volcano)   | ✅    | ✅          |
| HTML report (one file, all results)      | ❌    | ✅          |
| Reproducible (Nextflow + containers)     | ❌    | ✅          |
| CI/CD auto-container builds (GHCR)       | ❌    | ✅          |
| Multi-comparison support (samplesheet)   | ❌    | ✅          |

### Remaining genuine gaps vs Eleni

| Feature                                        | Eleni | Us  | Notes                                     |
|------------------------------------------------|-------|-----|-------------------------------------------|
| ISAR full functional annotation (PFAM, IUPred, SignalP) | ❌ | ✅ | PFAM + IUPred3 (Tier A); SignalP/DeepTMHMM deferred |
| LeafCutter (intron excision events)            | ✅    | ✅  | Modules + subworkflow + report section complete |

