## Next: ISAR full functional annotation (TODO-1 from PIPELINE_PLAN.md)

This is the biggest remaining analytical gap. Currently isar_switch_consequences.R
only computes: intron_retention, coding_potential, ORF_seq_similarity, NMD_status.

Full annotation adds: domains_identified, domain_isotype (PFAM),
IDR_identified, IDR_type (IUPred2A/3), signal_peptide_identified (SignalP),
topology_identified (DeepTMHMM).

### Feasibility tiers

Tier A — free, easy to containerize, high value:
- [x] PFAM via HMMER (bioconda::hmmer + Pfam-A.hmm provided by user ~500 MB)
      → analyzePFAM() in ISAR; adds domain gain/loss consequences
- [x] IUPred2A/IUPred3 (free academic, conda-installable)
      → analyzeIUPred2A() in ISAR; adds IDR consequences
- [ ] CPC2 (free, replaces ISAR's built-in coding potential with a better caller)
      → analyzeCPC2() in ISAR (deferred to future iteration)

Tier B — institutional/registration, worth supporting as optional:
- [ ] SignalP 6.0 (DTU Health Tech, free for academic, needs manual download)
      → accept pre-computed result via --signalp_results param
- [ ] DeepTMHMM (free via Docker, BioLib API or local)
      → accept pre-computed result via --deeptmhmm_results param

Implementation plan for Tier A:
- [x] F1  Add HMMER + Pfam-A.hmm container block to isar Dockerfile
- [x] F2  Create modules/local/isar_run_pfam/main.nf — runs hmmscan on AA FASTA
- [x] F3  Create modules/local/isar_run_iupred/main.nf — runs iupred3 on AA FASTA
- [x] F4  Add analyzePFAM() + analyzeIUPred2A() calls to isar_switch_consequences.R
- [x] F5  Add --run_isar_full_annotation boolean param (default: false) — gates F1-F4
- [x] F6  Add --pfam_hmm param for user-provided Pfam-A.hmm path
- [x] F7  Wire into isoformswitchr_analysis subworkflow behind the flag

