## Next: LeafCutter integration

LeafCutter quantifies intron usage ratios (not exon inclusion like rMATS) and is
especially sensitive to complex splicing patterns and unannotated introns.
It complements rMATS well and is already part of many published splicing workflows.

- [x] L1  Create containers/leafcutter/Dockerfile (Python 3 + R leafcutter bioconductor pkg)
- [x] L2  Create modules/local/leafcutter_bam2junc/main.nf — per-sample BAM → junc conversion
- [x] L3  Create modules/local/leafcutter_cluster/main.nf — cluster introns across samples
- [x] L4  Create modules/local/leafcutter_ds/main.nf — differential splicing test
- [x] L5  Create subworkflows/local/leafcutter_analysis/main.nf
- [x] L6  Add --run_leafcutter param + wire into main workflow + sentinel fallback
- [x] L7  Add LeafCutter section to render_report.Rmd (deltaPSI distribution, top cluster table)
- [x] L8  Include LeafCutter genes in cross-tool UpSet plot

