## New ideas — within scope, reasonable effort

These are not blocking anything but would meaningfully improve the pipeline.

### I1 — VOILA interactive report link
After MAJIQ_DELTAPSI, optionally run `majiq-v3 voila` to produce a self-contained
HTML interactive browser for LSV exploration. Gate with --run_voila flag.
Effort: low (single new process, same container as MAJIQ).

### I2 — ISAR switch plots in HTML report
isar_switch_consequences.R already calls switchPlotTopN() and writes PDFs.
Embed the top 5 switch plots (convert PDF→PNG via imagemagick or use ggplot2
plots directly) into the Rmd report so reviewers see them without opening PDFs.
Effort: low-medium (R only, no new module).

### I3 — nf-core lint compliance
Add missing nf-core boilerplate: nextflow_schema.json, CITATIONS.md, .nf-core.yml.
Required before submitting to nf-core/pipelines or citing the pipeline in a paper.
Effort: medium (schema JSON is verbose but templated).

### I4 — Export TSV summary per comparison
After the report renders, publish a machine-readable TSV combining top hits from
rMATS + MAJIQ + ISAR into one unified table (gene, event_type, tool, dPSI, FDR).
Effort: low (R script addition to RENDER_REPORT process).

### I5 — Salmon bootstrap warning
In validate_samplesheet.py (or ISAR_IMPORT), check that quant.sf files have a
corresponding bootstrap_inferential_replicates directory. ISAR uses bootstraps for
the satuRn test uncertainty model; without them only point estimates are used.
Emit a clear WARNING rather than silently running without bootstraps.
Effort: low (Python, modify validate_samplesheet.py).

### I6 — Multi-organism support for GO/KEGG
Currently --organism only accepts 'human' or 'mouse'. Extend to rat, zebrafish,
fly, worm via org.Rn.eg.db, org.Dr.eg.db, org.Dm.eg.db, org.Ce.eg.db.
Add the packages to containers/report/Dockerfile and extend the Rmd switch block.
Effort: low.

